- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with measuring linguistic coordination in conversations using word embeddings. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is also likely as the paper explores the correlation between linguistic coordination and social behaviors/outcomes. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses neural word representations to measure linguistic coordination. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is possible as the paper applies its approach to case studies in the clinical psychology domain. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with spoken conversations.
